1404	    /// Tries to remove objects from an array using a field filter in the last
1405	    /// key segment.
1406	    ///
1407	    /// A key of the form `<array-key>/<field-name>=<field-value>` removes every
1408	    /// object from the array stored at `<array-key>` whose `<field-name>` field
1409	    /// is the string `<field-value>`. The `<field-name>` part is not a config
1410	    /// child key; it is a filter applied to objects contained in the array. For
1411	    /// example, `qos/network/id=rule1` removes objects from `qos/network` where
1412	    /// `id == "rule1"`.
